              "summary": "detect_impact's new source-focused seed filter is applied with zero disclosure anywhere in the response: pagination totals are post-filter, the formatter emits no note, and the tool description still says it merges git diffs 'into a changed-file set' with no mention of the default filter or the include_data opt-in.",
              "failure_scenario": "Caller changes only Cargo.toml and config/settings.yaml relative to origin/main and runs default detect_impact. merge_git_changed_paths returns 2 paths; filter_paths_by_prefix_and_language(..., true) drops both (Toml/Yaml are is_config_language). Response: 'Impact analysis: 0 changed file(s), 0 changed symbol(s), 0 blast-radius node(s)' — indistinguishable from a genuinely clean diff. Pre-dd132d6 the same call reported the files and their key-symbols. The agent concludes nothing changed; nothing in the reply, payload, or tool schema description hints that 2 changed paths were filtered or that include_data=true restores them.",
              "evidence": "git show a646f23:src/protocol/tools.rs lines 7266-7271: `let changed_files = if params.0.include_data.unwrap_or(false) { changed_files } else { filter_paths_by_prefix_and_language(changed_files.clone(), None, None, true).unwrap_or(changed_files) };` then `changed_files_total = changed_files.len()` (post-filter). git show a646f23:src/protocol/format.rs:2334 detect_impact_result: only base/staleness/truncation notes — grep for 'source|filter|include_data' in the formatter returns nothing. Tool description at tools.rs:7158 unchanged from pre-fix (no include_data / source-focus mention). Spec FR-009 (0f6023b:specs/018-dogfood-surface-hardening/spec.md:98) requires Constitution III disclosure preserved; the same commit implements exactly this disclosure for what_changed (scope summary) but not for detect_impact, and the commit message claims 'Keep disclosure honest'.",
              "why_tests_miss": "tests/detect_impact.rs::detect_impact_default_source_focuses_changed_set (added in dd132d6) asserts only the JSON payload contents (changed_files == [src/a.rs], no key symbols) and the include_data opt-in; no test asserts any disclosure text, and no test covers the all-data-changed case where the response degenerates to all-zeros.",
              "minimal_fix": "Capture pre-filter count before the filter; when it differs from post-filter, append a note line in detect_impact_result (e.g. 'note: N non-source changed path(s) excluded (source-focused default; pass include_data=true to include)') and/or a payload field; add the default + include_data to the #[tool] description and a dated addendum to specs/015-cbm-capability-ports/contracts/detect-impact.md.",
