              "failure_scenario": "Agent's only dirty file is data/config.json (or deploy.sh). Plain what_changed() resolves to Uncommitted mode with code_only defaulting true (tools.rs:7015); filtered is empty while total_paths=1, so the handler returns the bare 'matched the requested filters' string with no envelope. Pre-dd132d6 this branch was reachable only when the caller actually passed a filter, so the wording was accurate; now a no-args caller is told their (real, git-visible) changes matched no 'requested' filters and has no in-band way to learn why or how to opt out. The disclosure the 018 contract promises ('the envelope continues to state ... that a filter was applied', tool-behavior.md:12) exists only on the non-empty path.",
              "evidence": "git show a646f23:src/protocol/tools.rs:7015 `params.0.code_only.unwrap_or(true)`; :7017-7025 empty-path early return with the two bare strings (no format_search_envelope call); :6879 tool description unchanged ('Set code_only=true to exclude non-source files'); :466-469 code_only field doc unchanged. Pre-state confirmed via git show dd132d6^:src/protocol/tools.rs:7035 `unwrap_or(false)` with the identical message strings.",
              "why_tests_miss": "dd132d6's test_what_changed_uncommitted_default_excludes_data_files asserts the exact string 'No uncommitted changes matched the requested filters.' as the EXPECTED output, blessing the misleading wording; the disclosure test (test_what_changed_uncommitted_default_discloses_code_only_filter) only covers the non-empty path where the envelope exists.",
              "minimal_fix": "On the uncommitted default-filtered empty path, return a self-describing message, e.g. 'No uncommitted source changes; {total_paths} non-source path(s) excluded by the default code-only filter (pass code_only=false to include them).' and update the tool description / code_only doc to state the uncommitted-mode default.",
