              "summary": "The code_only classifier treats every unrecognized extension as non-source (`None => return false`), so the new defaults silently hide legitimate SOURCE file classes — .sql, .sh, .ps1, .proto, .tf, Dockerfile, Makefile, extensionless scripts — from default what_changed(uncommitted) listings and detect_impact changed_files, though spec FR-001 scopes the flip to 'non-source data files'.",
              "failure_scenario": "Agent edits migrations/001_add_users.sql plus src/lib.rs and runs default what_changed: only src/lib.rs is listed (the .sql migration vanishes; envelope says 'code-only filter ... 1 of 2 path(s) shown' but not WHICH class was dropped). Agent edits only deploy.sh: reply is the misleading zero-hit string from the previous finding. Same class disappears from detect_impact's changed_files. Pre-dd132d6, both tools listed these files by default; the agent's 'what did I change?' answer is now silently incomplete for every non-indexed source language.",
              "evidence": "git show a646f23:src/protocol/tools.rs:758-768: `if code_only && lang_filter.is_none() { let ext = path.rsplit('.').next().unwrap_or(\"\"); match LanguageId::from_extension(ext) { None => return false, Some(lang) => { if is_config_language(&lang) { return false; } } } }`. git show a646f23:src/domain/index.rs:35-64 from_extension: 24 extensions, none of sql/sh/ps1/proto/tf; extensionless paths yield ext=whole-path -> None. Spec text (0f6023b:specs/018-dogfood-surface-hardening/spec.md:90, FR-001): default must exclude 'non-source data files' — a shell script or SQL migration is source, not data. build.rs (.rs) and Html/Css/Scss are correctly retained.",
              "why_tests_miss": "Every US1 test (tools.rs mod tests and tests/detect_impact.rs) uses .json as the excluded file; no test exercises an unknown-extension source file (.sh/.sql/Dockerfile) against the new defaults, so the over-broad classification is never observed.",
              "minimal_fix": "Either narrow the default exclusion to known data formats (drop only is_config_language matches plus a small binary/lock allowlist, keep unknown extensions) at the two default call sites, or — smaller — keep the semantics but disclose the excluded class/count per the two disclosure fixes above and document that code_only means 'recognized programming-language extensions only'.",
              "confidence": "high"
