              "failure_scenario": "A reviewer or future implementer validating against tool-behavior.md US2 ('Delta: ... results are ranked by (reference_count desc, kind_priority, path, line)'; 'Input: unchanged') writes a conformance check expecting two same-named structs in different files to both appear in a browse page; actual behavior (search.rs:943-944 retain over a seen HashSet) returns one, with no truncation signal since total_matches is counted after dedup. Similarly contracts/detect-impact.md still documents the input struct and 'Git path union: merge_git_changed_paths' with no include_data field or seed filter, while the tool description points to it as the authoritative frozen contract.",
              "evidence": "git show a646f23:src/live_index/search.rs:943-944 `let mut seen = HashSet::new(); matches.retain(|candidate| seen.insert((candidate.name.clone(), candidate.kind.clone())));` (before `total_matches = matches.len()`); git show a646f23:specs/018-dogfood-surface-hardening/contracts/tool-behavior.md:23-27 (no dedup mention); `git grep -in 'dedup|representative' 0f6023b -- specs/018-dogfood-surface-hardening/` returns nothing; contracts/detect-impact.md at a646f23 has a '## Addendum — 2026-07-02' section but nothing for the dd132d6 change. The search_symbols #[tool] description WAS updated ('returns one representative per exact name+kind'), so the schema surface is honest — only the spec contracts drifted.",
              "why_tests_miss": "Tests assert the implemented dedup behavior (test_browse_deduplicates_repeated_generic_names) — nothing checks spec artifacts against code, so contract drift is invisible to CI.",
