            "truncate_text_at_line_boundary (format.rs:4802-4823 at f5cad59) iterates char_indices and breaks when char_end > max_bytes — no mid-char slice, no UTF-8 panic, and the empty-cut edge (first char larger than budget) yields \"\" safely.",
            "symforge_retrieve miss path (tools.rs:10283-10295 at f5cad59) validates the 12-hex handle and returns a clear 'unknown or expired hash' message instead of panicking on an evicted blob.",
            "Both new size checks use the same threshold (len <= tokens*4 with saturating_mul), so there is no gap where enforce_token_budget truncates but the CCR wrapper returned early, and no case where the footer is emitted without truncation.",
            "No downstream re-truncation strips the footer: the five CCR builders return apply_ccr_budget output directly, and the compact facade's finalize_symforge_output (stel/handler.rs:156) only prepends the trust envelope."
