              "failure_scenario": "Run `cargo test --all-targets -- --test-threads=1` on the default dogfood machine where a real symforge daemon is running (this repo's documented topology). The test calls index_folder against http://127.0.0.1:1; the first proxy attempt fails; because the client was built `.with_project_root(home_root.clone())` (frozen line 8322), proxy_tool_call proceeds to `reconnect()` -> `connect_or_spawn_session` -> `ensure_daemon_running()` against the unguarded real SYMFORGE_HOME: (a) `daemon_port_if_compatible` finds the real daemon reachable but identity-mismatched (test-binary exe path != daemon exe path); (b) `stop_incompatible_recorded_daemon` refuses to kill it (executable-name gate) but then UNCONDITIONALLY calls `cleanup_daemon_runtime_files()`, deleting the real daemon's port, pid, AND auth-token files — the live daemon keeps running but becomes undiscoverable, so the next real client spawns a duplicate daemon (two daemons persisting snapshots for the same projects); (c) `spawn_daemon_process()` then launches `std::env::current_exe()` — the libtest binary — detached with arg \"daemon\", i.e. a nested unsupervised parallel run of every test whose name contains \"daemon\"; (d) `wait_for_daemon_ready` stalls ~5s before the reconnect fails. These side effects persist even after the intended refusal implementation lands, because the refusal can only happen after proxy_tool_call (and its reconnect attempt) returns None.",
